==Hilts==
Looking for sourcing to substantiate the view that Jones inspired the Hilts character. [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1514150/PoW-pilot-who-inspired-the-Great-Escape-dies-at-the-age-of-102.html This article] points to another prisoner. [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/10799031/William-Ash-obituary.html ''This article''] points to yet another! We clearly need better sourcing. There are some superficial-looking Hollywood books referring to Jones but given the conflict in sourcing I'd like to see one directly quoting a person involved in the production stating that Jones was the model for, or among the models for, the Steve McQueen-Virgil Hilts character. A Youtube video is insufficient. [[User:Coretheapple|Coretheapple]] ([[User talk:Coretheapple|talk]]) 14:48, 27 August 2016 (UTC)

[https://books.google.com/books?id=GfUDb5iivEQC&pg=PA46&dq=virgil+hilts&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVhdbY7OHOAhXKFh4KHZW9CYAQ6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=virgil%20hilts&f=false Here] is another. That makes four including Jones and I'm still looking. Apparently every American involved in the escape has been referred to as a model for Hilts.  [[User:Coretheapple|Coretheapple]] ([[User talk:Coretheapple|talk]]) 14:55, 27 August 2016 (UTC)
